SUMMARY:602 planning [@mtg]
DESCRIPTION:1. incoming class appears to be 10 students (5 groups of 2?)\n2
 . ☑ review labs and supporting materials\n   • SEM/TEM sample prep is time
  consuming\n3. Hoagland will ask Reika about her two labs\n   • Hoagland t
 ake Rheology+Molding/Tensile\; Calorimetry\n4. ☑ review videos: Katsumata 
 videos in Canvas give error re: cookies\n   • SEM/TEM videos show sample p
 rep steps\; loading etc\n   • Light scattering video is about 40 min!\n5. 
 should we continue reviewing cycle?  this impacts the matrix\n6. next time
 \, once labs are finalized\, to identify TAs\n7. should we shrink labs?\n 
   • based on what criteria: student interactiveness\, student\n     intere
 st\, most broadly central to polymer science\, etc\n8. 2 EA\, 2 FR\, 2 pre
 sentations: should we give the students a "good\n   example"\n   • can use
  highest marks from 2025 to choose.\n9. AI:\n   • ☑ what is current policy
 /guideline?\n     • University has "Guidance on Generative AI"\n   • ☑ re:
  policy/guideline\, particularly for writing/plaigarism:\n     • nothing e
 xplicit\, so we'd have to include this ourselves for\n       our specific 
 course.
CATEGORIES:@mtg,602
SEQUENCE:1
PRIORITY:5
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
END:VTODO
